A man has died after a shooting outside Queensbury tube station in north-west London. Police launched a murder investigation after the victim, believed to be in his thirties, was found with critical injuries on Tuesday night. Another man, aged in his 20s, was hospitalised with a gunshot wound. Scotland Yard said officers were called to the scene on Cumberland Road just after 9pm on Tuesday. They found the older man with serious injuries and he died at the scene almost an hour later. The younger man attended a north London hospital and was in a stable condition, police said. A crime scene was declared on Cumberland Road and Essoldo Way where police said the attacks were believed to have taken place. Metropolitan police officers were examining CCTV footage and called for anyone with information to come forward.